  "text": "Different from mechanism of symptomatic HT, we speculate that AHT may link with small artery formation rather than large artery formation. It has been showed that thrombolysis after acute ischemic infarction may lead to artery reopening and collateral circulation reperfusion6 [CITATION_1] . Moreover, the formation of collateral circulation may also improve the functional outcome. There is a favorable trend after thrombolysis-related AHT in our study supports this suggestion.",
